00:32:53,370 --> 00:32:54,769
lt sure is.

498
00:32:55,050 --> 00:32:57,769
She was right behind
this same counter.

499
00:32:58,050 --> 00:33:00,689
Almost six years ago exactly.

500
00:33:01,090 --> 00:33:02,079
Mr. Pocum says. . .

501
00:33:02,370 --> 00:33:03,962
. . .the needle's too good for him.

502
00:33:04,250 --> 00:33:05,649
For Beechum.

503
00:33:05,930 --> 00:33:08,490
They ought to bring back the chair.
That's what l say.

504
00:33:08,770 --> 00:33:11,204
Really let him have
a jolt of something.

505
00:33:11,490 --> 00:33:12,559
What's back there?

506
00:33:13,170 --> 00:33:14,080
Bathroom.

507
00:33:14,370 --> 00:33:15,644
Mr. Pocum was always nice. . .

508
00:33:15,930 --> 00:33:18,922
. . .about letting folks come in
and do their business.

509
00:33:19,810 --> 00:33:24,361
l'll come back some other time maybe
and do some really serious shopping.

510
00:33:24,810 --> 00:33:26,801
Am l going to be in the newspaper?

511
00:33:27,890 --> 00:33:29,084
Was something here before?

512
00:33:29,370 --> 00:33:31,486
That's where
the potato chips used to be.

513
00:33:31,770 --> 00:33:34,079
But Mr. Pocum moved
the rack over here. . .

514
00:33:34,370 --> 00:33:36,122
. . .so it'd be what you call. . .

515
00:33:36,410 --> 00:33:39,049
. . .an impulse kind of purchase.

516
00:33:39,570 --> 00:33:41,401
This in that story you're writing?

517
00:33:42,930 --> 00:33:44,488
That's a good point.

518
00:33:44,770 --> 00:33:47,807
l'm writing a human-interest sidebar.
Do you know what that is?

519
00:33:48,290 --> 00:33:49,564
No, l don't think l do.

520
00:33:49,850 --> 00:33:51,727
l don't think l do either.

521
00:34:09,810 --> 00:34:11,323
Sorry, l got hung up.

522
00:34:12,290 --> 00:34:13,405
Daddy!

523
00:34:13,690 --> 00:34:15,521
Aren't we going to the zoo today?

524
00:34:15,810 --> 00:34:19,485
Well, what's holding us up?
Don't you want to get dressed?

525
00:34:19,770 --> 00:34:23,160
-Let's change your clothes.
-What animal do you want to see?

526
00:34:23,450 --> 00:34:25,725
Daddy, l want to go see
the hippopotamus.

527
00:34:26,010 --> 00:34:27,762
Come on, let's change your pants.

528
00:34:32,850 --> 00:34:35,410
l tell you,
looking into those eyes...

529
00:34:35,690 --> 00:34:37,009
...l don 't think....

530
00:34:38,050 --> 00:34:42,441
lt was like looking into the eyes
of a goat. Something like that.

531
00:34:43,090 --> 00:34:44,967
They were that cold.

532
00:34:45,570 --> 00:34:48,846
l can 't honestly say that
l've ever wished anyone dead.

533
00:34:49,130 --> 00:34:52,964
But l think l'll feel a lot safer
when Frank Beechum 's gone.

534
00:34:53,810 --> 00:34:57,598
That's Dale Porterhouse, an accountant
with the firm of Stokes and Whitney.

535
00:34:57,890 --> 00:35:02,247
Porterhouse was the state's key witness
in the Wilson case six years ago...

536
00:35:02,530 --> 00:35:06,045
...a case that will culminate
at one minute past midnight...

537
00:35:06,330 --> 00:35:10,209
... with the execution by lethal
injection of Frank Beechum.

538
00:35:10,490 --> 00:35:12,128
lnformation. What city, please?

539
00:35:12,410 --> 00:35:16,528
Oakland, for a Stokes and Whitney.
lt's an accounting firm.

540
00:35:16,810 --> 00:35:18,528
The number you requested is....

541
00:35:18,810 --> 00:35:20,607
Come on, let's go. Daddy's here.

542
00:35:20,890 --> 00:35:22,005
Steve, what is it?

543
00:35:22,290 --> 00:35:24,201
Just a hunch l've got.
Bear with me.

544
00:35:24,650 --> 00:35:26,845
Tonight, finally, is the execution.

545
00:35:27,130 --> 00:35:30,839
lt's been a long six years. Do you
feeljustice is finally being done?

546
00:35:31,130 --> 00:35:33,086
ls Dale Porterhouse there, please?

547
00:35:33,370 --> 00:35:36,407
-Mr. Porterhouse is at lunch.
-Get off the phone, Daddy.

548
00:35:37,970 --> 00:35:39,608
Right now!

549
00:35:40,810 --> 00:35:45,088
This is Steve Everett. l'm a reporter
with the Oakland Tribune.

550
00:35:45,370 --> 00:35:48,203
Could you have him call me?
lt's about the Beechum case.

551
00:35:48,490 --> 00:35:51,527
Nothing will end that rage
except the death of the monster...

552
00:35:51,810 --> 00:35:54,529
... who killed my daughter
and my unborn grandchild.

553
00:35:54,970 --> 00:35:56,369
l'll give you my beeper number.

554
00:35:57,170 --> 00:35:58,683
You're not taking that beeper!

555
00:35:58,970 --> 00:36:02,167
Just a second, it's just a hunch.
No big deal.

556
00:36:03,690 --> 00:36:05,362
Yeah, it's 5-5-5. . .

557
00:36:05,890 --> 00:36:07,243
. . . 1 -4-3-9.

558
00:36:07,530 --> 00:36:09,248
-l'll make sure he gets it.
-Thanks.

559
00:36:10,210 --> 00:36:12,599
Okay, sweetheart, what do you think?

560
00:36:12,930 --> 00:36:15,808
Are you ready for the big hippo?

561
00:36:16,730 --> 00:36:18,846
You want to go in the den with Dad?

562
00:36:19,130 --> 00:36:22,406
l'll show you something
Dad's got to take with him.

563
00:36:23,290 --> 00:36:25,850
Not the beeper.
Right? Not the beeper.

564
00:36:26,130 --> 00:36:29,566
Let's pick up my beeper.
This goes ''beep, beep, beep. ''

565
00:36:32,410 --> 00:36:34,560
Yeah, it goes ''beep, beep, beep. ''

566
00:36:35,570 --> 00:36:37,845
Come on, get your jacket on.

567
00:36:38,130 --> 00:36:41,964
And now we're just hours away
from the actual time of execution.

568
00:36:42,250 --> 00:36:44,639
Daddy, l want to go see
the hippopotamus.

569
00:36:44,930 --> 00:36:47,398
After a break,
we'll be talking to someone...

570
00:36:47,690 --> 00:36:50,409
... who thinks capital punishment
is never the solution.

571
00:36:50,690 --> 00:36:52,362
l love you!

572
00:36:53,970 --> 00:36:55,562
Bye, Katie!

573
00:36:56,410 --> 00:36:58,640
Have a good time! l love you.

574
00:36:58,930 --> 00:37:00,648
l love you too, Mama.

575
00:37:02,210 --> 00:37:03,438
Wait!

576
00:37:04,570 --> 00:37:05,525
The car seat!

577
00:37:06,410 --> 00:37:08,207
Mother, l'm too big for a car seat.

578
00:37:08,490 --> 00:37:10,162
We'll put her in back.
How's that?

579
00:37:10,690 --> 00:37:12,681
Put her in the back seat.
Seat belt!

580
00:37:14,450 --> 00:37:16,839
Don't forget the seat belt!

581
00:37:20,290 --> 00:37:21,518
The seat belt, Steven!

582
00:37:21,850 --> 00:37:23,283
lt's fine. lt's fine.

583
00:37:23,570 --> 00:37:25,367
l should've never
stopped by that store.

584
00:37:26,530 --> 00:37:27,679
Oh, God!

585
00:37:33,570 --> 00:37:37,358
Dale Porterhouse, please. This is
Steve Everett of the Tribune.

586
00:37:38,610 --> 00:37:41,408
Be with you
in just a second, darling.

587
00:37:41,690 --> 00:37:44,409
This is Dale Porterhouse.
What can l do for you?

588
00:37:45,530 --> 00:37:48,522
l'll be ready in a second, darling.
We'll go in a second.

589
00:37:48,810 --> 00:37:51,608
Mr. Porterhouse, this is Steve Everett
of the Tribune.

590
00:37:51,890 --> 00:37:55,041
l'm covering the Beechum
execution tonight.

591
00:37:56,410 --> 00:37:59,880
l thought you were one of
the chief witnesses in that.

592
00:38:00,970 --> 00:38:03,609
Just a second.
Just a second, sweetheart.

593
00:38:04,770 --> 00:38:07,967
l was wondering if l could have
1 0 minutes with you.

594
00:38:08,250 --> 00:38:10,718
l'd be glad to.
l can 't talk right now.

595
00:38:11,010 --> 00:38:12,363
l could meet you later.

596
00:38:12,570 --> 00:38:13,400
Yeah, where?

597
00:38:13,850 --> 00:38:17,604
How about we meet at the
Bread Company restaurant? Know it?

598
00:38:17,890 --> 00:38:19,642
Yeah, l know it exactly.

599
00:38:20,570 --> 00:38:22,162
On Ninth Street, isn't it?

600
00:38:22,890 --> 00:38:26,007
-How about we meet in a half-hour?
-Half-hour it'll be.

601
00:38:27,010 --> 00:38:28,443
Thanks. Bye.

602
00:38:29,010 --> 00:38:29,886
Okay, baby.

603
00:38:30,170 --> 00:38:31,728
Come here. Come on.

604
00:38:32,890 --> 00:38:35,040
But l'm too big to sit in a stroller!

605
00:38:35,370 --> 00:38:38,885
That's nonsense. We're going
to play this game called Speed Zoo.

606
00:38:39,170 --> 00:38:40,808
Speed Zoo?

607
00:38:42,690 --> 00:38:44,089
Monkeys!

608
00:38:52,170 --> 00:38:54,684
-Giraffes!
-We go fast.

609
00:38:57,690 --> 00:38:58,805
Birdies!

610
00:38:59,090 --> 00:39:00,239
Speed Zoo!

611
00:39:01,770 --> 00:39:02,885
Camel lips!

612
00:39:07,610 --> 00:39:09,089
We go fast.

613
00:39:09,530 --> 00:39:10,929
We go fast!

614
00:39:12,210 --> 00:39:14,166
Where's the hippopotamus?

615
00:39:14,450 --> 00:39:16,566
Elephants! Look at the elephants.

616
00:39:17,170 --> 00:39:18,842
Where's the hippopotamus?

617
00:39:19,130 --> 00:39:20,483
Speed Zoo!

618
00:39:21,090 --> 00:39:23,046
l want to see the hippopotamus!

619
00:39:23,410 --> 00:39:24,729
We go fast.

620
00:39:25,010 --> 00:39:26,648
l want a hippopotamus!

621
00:39:39,530 --> 00:39:42,567
l'm sorry. l wouldn't have
this happen for the world.

622
00:39:44,410 --> 00:39:45,559
l want my mommy!

623
00:39:45,850 --> 00:39:47,568
l know, sweetie.

624
00:39:48,850 --> 00:39:49,839
Daddy's sorry.

625
00:39:54,130 --> 00:39:56,564
Oh, my God! What happened to you?

626
00:39:56,970 --> 00:39:59,643
She's a real trooper,
l've got to tell you.

627
00:40:00,250 --> 00:40:01,888
What the hell's wrong with you?

628
00:40:58,170 --> 00:40:59,603
How you holding up?

629
00:41:04,970 --> 00:41:07,404
Like l said, there's always a chance.

630
00:41:08,890 --> 00:41:10,960
But with all the feeling
about the girl. . . .

631
00:41:11,650 --> 00:41:14,562
You know how the governor's
tough on crime.

632
00:41:15,330 --> 00:41:17,560
So Mr. Berris says that maybe. . .

633
00:41:17,850 --> 00:41:21,365
. . .if you just tell him
about how remorseful you feel. . . .

634
00:41:21,730 --> 00:41:23,129
You know what l'm saying?

635
00:41:24,050 --> 00:41:26,086
-l didn't do it.
-l understand.

636
00:41:26,370 --> 00:41:29,919
l'm just telling you that's what
we're facing here, all right?

637
00:41:32,130 --> 00:41:34,644
l can't say l'm sorry
for what l never did.

638
00:41:36,010 --> 00:41:38,763
l'll call you as soon as
the appeal comes down.

639
00:41:39,050 --> 00:41:40,005
Hi, Daddy.

640
00:41:40,290 --> 00:41:42,850
l brought you a picture,
but it's not done. . .

641
00:41:43,130 --> 00:41:45,086
. . .so l have to finish it, okay?

642
00:41:47,010 --> 00:41:48,841
Hold on.
They're going to let me in.

643
00:41:53,130 --> 00:41:56,327
Don't be sad now.
We're not going to be afraid.

644
00:41:56,890 --> 00:41:59,643
Give Daddy a big hug, please?

645
00:42:02,770 --> 00:42:06,729
Come on, don't be sad. Don't be afraid.
We're not gonna be afraid.

646
00:42:07,250 --> 00:42:10,401
l'm gonna finish my picture now,
Daddy, okay?

647
00:42:10,890 --> 00:42:14,678
You do Daddy a favor, okay?
Now, walk over here with me, okay?

648
00:42:19,290 --> 00:42:23,568
l want you to sit right here while
l have a little talk with Mommy, okay?

649
00:42:25,770 --> 00:42:27,123
Give me a kiss.

650
00:42:33,850 --> 00:42:35,169
Come on.

651
00:42:36,530 --> 00:42:37,440
Come on, now.

652
00:42:38,530 --> 00:42:41,761
You know l'm just going home
to dreamland, that's all.

653
00:42:44,970 --> 00:42:48,007
lt's green pastures, Daddy. See?

654
00:42:48,290 --> 00:42:51,202
Here's the blue sky.
l made it at the motel.

655
00:42:51,690 --> 00:42:55,160
Gonna be holding two places
at the table for us.

656
00:42:58,290 --> 00:42:59,325
We're not gonna cry.

657
00:42:59,610 --> 00:43:01,168
l'm sorry. Okay.

658
00:43:01,490 --> 00:43:04,960
We know l'm going to a better place
beyond this place, right?

659
00:43:09,450 --> 00:43:11,839
The thing l worry about most
in all this. . . .

660
00:43:16,770 --> 00:43:19,000
No, she loves you.

661
00:43:19,410 --> 00:43:21,366
She loves you.

662
00:43:22,570 --> 00:43:25,084
l don't want her
to ever think her daddy did--

663
00:43:25,370 --> 00:43:27,008
She won't think that.

664
00:43:27,810 --> 00:43:29,368
She knows you.

665
00:43:29,730 --> 00:43:32,722
l can't find green, Mama.
Do you have it?

666
00:43:34,730 --> 00:43:37,847
All the crayons are
in the box, honey.

667
00:43:38,450 --> 00:43:40,088
Well, l can't find it.

668
00:43:41,930 --> 00:43:44,205
Don't you ever let her think it.

669
00:43:45,210 --> 00:43:46,438
You do that for me, okay?

670
00:43:46,770 --> 00:43:47,998
l swear.

671
00:43:49,010 --> 00:43:49,806
lt's lost.

672
00:43:50,090 --> 00:43:51,842
l can't find it anywhere.

673
00:43:52,410 --> 00:43:54,765
Can you use another color, honey?

674
00:43:55,450 --> 00:43:57,281
l have to have green.

675
00:43:57,570 --> 00:43:59,640
lt's green pastures!

676
00:44:00,930 --> 00:44:03,285
Look for it.
lt's got to be here somewhere.

677
00:44:03,570 --> 00:44:05,765
Daddy won't mind
if you use another color.

678
00:44:08,090 --> 00:44:09,443
Okay, baby.

679
00:44:10,450 --> 00:44:11,883
Calm down.

680
00:44:12,370 --> 00:44:14,008
Calm down, honey.

681
00:44:16,370 --> 00:44:17,120
Mrs. Beechum?

682
00:44:19,250 --> 00:44:21,206
What parking area did you use?

683
00:44:38,690 --> 00:44:40,043
Yeah, just a moment.

684
00:44:43,450 --> 00:44:45,042
lt's your lawyer again.

685
00:44:58,130 --> 00:44:59,199
We lost it.

686
00:45:00,090 --> 00:45:01,239
l'm sorry.

687
00:45:03,290 --> 00:45:06,202
Mr. Berris will be at the
governor's late this afternoon.

688
00:45:08,570 --> 00:45:11,004
We got to be honest
about what's going on.

689
00:45:11,530 --> 00:45:12,599
Know what l'm saying?

690
00:45:17,570 --> 00:45:19,481
l'm really sorry, Frank.

691
00:45:20,610 --> 00:45:23,841
We tried, but you know,
itjust didn 't work.

692
00:45:24,690 --> 00:45:27,841
l don 't know what else to say.
l'm so sorry.

693
00:45:28,850 --> 00:45:30,329
God bless you, Frank.

694
00:45:36,850 --> 00:45:40,126
-So is there anything?
-No, nothing yet.

695
00:45:40,410 --> 00:45:43,482
You know how these legal things are.
They take forever.

696
00:45:48,410 --> 00:45:50,640
Control, we've located the material.

697
00:45:54,970 --> 00:45:56,198
Copy that.

698
00:45:57,610 --> 00:45:58,360
Good news.

699
00:46:00,170 --> 00:46:02,126
They found the crayon.
lt'll be here soon.

700
00:46:05,010 --> 00:46:06,443
You hear that, sweetie?

701
00:46:06,730 --> 00:46:10,086
Now you can show Daddy
some real pastures.

702
00:46:10,490 --> 00:46:15,006
-Green pastures.
-That's right. Baby's green pastures.

703
00:46:15,290 --> 00:46:16,439
Come here.

704
00:46:20,930 --> 00:46:22,602
Your green is coming.

705
00:46:22,890 --> 00:46:24,687
Told you they would find it.

706
00:46:31,650 --> 00:46:34,881
l believe there's such a thing
in this world as good citizenship.

707
00:46:35,170 --> 00:46:39,049
A man sees an injustice, let alone
a cold-blooded murder, he has--

708
00:46:39,370 --> 00:46:42,203
Let me get this straight.
You didn't see the murder.

709
00:46:42,490 --> 00:46:45,050
Of course not.
l never said l did.

710
00:46:45,370 --> 00:46:46,519
Well, what did you see?

711
00:46:46,810 --> 00:46:49,449
Mr. Everett, l've been
through this so many times.

712
00:46:49,730 --> 00:46:53,609
-l can't tell you how many--
-l have trouble getting it into my head.

713
00:46:53,890 --> 00:46:55,084
lt's simple.

714
00:46:55,490 --> 00:46:57,845
l went into Pocum's to use the phone.

715
00:46:58,290 --> 00:47:00,008
My car had overheated.

716
00:47:00,290 --> 00:47:04,203
When the door slammed behind me,
he jumped up from behind the counter.

717
00:47:04,530 --> 00:47:06,407
He was covered with blood
and had a gun.

718
00:47:07,050 --> 00:47:09,359
l guess it was when
he was bending over Amy. . .

719
00:47:09,770 --> 00:47:12,762
...l mean, Mrs. Wilson,
stealing her ring and her necklace.

720
00:47:13,090 --> 00:47:16,480
He got one good look at me,
then ran out the service entrance.

721
00:47:16,770 --> 00:47:21,127
My concern is for the girl,
so l immediately dial 91 1.

722
00:47:23,250 --> 00:47:24,080
l figured...

723
00:47:24,370 --> 00:47:26,884
... why should l run after a killer
who 's got a gun...

724
00:47:27,210 --> 00:47:29,121
. . .when l can let
the police do their job?

725
00:47:29,410 --> 00:47:30,684
And they sure did it.

726
00:47:31,010 --> 00:47:32,602
Yeah, they sure did.

727
00:47:32,890 --> 00:47:35,484
We live in a country
where there's a rule of law.

728
00:47:35,770 --> 00:47:38,842
l mean, an ordinary citizen
who does--

729
00:47:39,130 --> 00:47:41,963
Aren't you going to take notes
or use a tape recorder?

730
00:47:42,250 --> 00:47:43,922
Usually when l talk to reporters. . .

731
00:47:44,210 --> 00:47:47,008
. . .they want to keep a record
of what l say.

732
00:47:47,730 --> 00:47:49,686
l've got a photographic memory.

733
00:47:50,290 --> 00:47:51,609
ls that some kind of joke?

734
00:47:54,090 --> 00:47:56,001
No, l have a notebook right here.

735
00:47:56,330 --> 00:47:59,163
Just having an off day.
You'll have to excuse me.

736
00:48:02,010 --> 00:48:02,806
Slow day.

737
00:48:03,410 --> 00:48:04,638
Yeah, well. . . .

738
00:48:06,490 --> 00:48:09,721
-My point simply was this: A man--
-Mr. Porterhouse. . .

739
00:48:10,050 --> 00:48:11,847
. . .let me cut to the chase.

740
00:48:12,890 --> 00:48:15,529
Are you absolutely sure
about your testimony?

741
00:48:16,650 --> 00:48:18,368
Absolutely. Why wouldn't l be?

742
00:48:18,850 --> 00:48:22,240
You saw Frank Beechum's face
and the gun?

743
00:48:23,770 --> 00:48:27,558
lf l had doubts about my testimony,
l would've told the police.

744
00:48:28,650 --> 00:48:32,165
That must have been scary, having him
