Fear of pain.

989
01:05:12,290 --> 01:05:14,281
Fear of prison.

990
01:05:15,490 --> 01:05:17,924
Fear of being separated
from my loved ones.

991
01:05:19,890 --> 01:05:22,358
All those fears rolled up into one.

992
01:05:24,450 --> 01:05:28,159
Never having a chance to see
my daughter draw pictures like this.

993
01:05:32,290 --> 01:05:34,520
She says it's Green Pastures.

994
01:05:44,290 --> 01:05:46,167
l want to tell everyone that. . .

995
01:05:46,410 --> 01:05:49,208
. . .l believe in Jesus Christ,
our Lord and Savior.

996
01:05:55,290 --> 01:05:58,362
l believe l'm going to a better place.

997
01:06:00,530 --> 01:06:04,125
And there's a better place,
better justice there.

998
01:06:05,530 --> 01:06:06,758
l came into my faith. . .

999
01:06:07,010 --> 01:06:08,409
. . .late in life.

1000
01:06:10,210 --> 01:06:13,327
Did a lot of bad things
when l was younger. You know?

1001
01:06:14,690 --> 01:06:16,009
Anyway. . .

1002
01:06:17,530 --> 01:06:20,044
. . .l believe the crookeds will
be made straight.

1003
01:06:20,290 --> 01:06:23,362
That's what the Bible says.
l believe that.

1004
01:06:29,090 --> 01:06:31,001
So that's how l feel about it.

1005
01:06:34,370 --> 01:06:36,201
ls that all right, Mr. Everett?

1006
01:06:36,530 --> 01:06:37,804
You got nine more minutes.

1007
01:06:42,930 --> 01:06:45,205
l mean, is there any more
that you want?

1008
01:06:48,610 --> 01:06:50,760
Mr. Beechum, you don't know me.

1009
01:06:51,730 --> 01:06:54,039
l'm just a guy out there
with a screw loose.

1010
01:06:56,690 --> 01:06:59,568
Frankly, l don't give a rat's ass
about Jesus Christ. . .

1011
01:06:59,810 --> 01:07:02,802
. . .and l don't care about
justice in this world or the next.

1012
01:07:03,050 --> 01:07:05,769
l don't even care what's right or wrong.
Never have.

1013
01:07:06,610 --> 01:07:07,929
But you know what this is?

1014
01:07:10,050 --> 01:07:11,802
What is this, some kind of joke?

1015
01:07:12,050 --> 01:07:14,723
No, it's no joke.
That's my nose.

1016
01:07:14,970 --> 01:07:18,485
To tell you the pitiful truth,
that's all l have in life.

1017
01:07:19,890 --> 01:07:21,767
When it tells me something stinks. . .

1018
01:07:22,010 --> 01:07:24,888
. . .l have faith in it,
like you have faith in Jesus.

1019
01:07:25,970 --> 01:07:30,009
When my nose is working well,
l know there's truth there somewhere.

1020
01:07:31,050 --> 01:07:32,563
But if it isn't working. . .

1021
01:07:33,170 --> 01:07:36,082
. . .you may as well drive me off a cliff.
l'm nothing.

1022
01:07:38,450 --> 01:07:39,280
Lately. . .

1023
01:07:39,850 --> 01:07:41,169
. . .l'm not 1 00% sure. . .

1024
01:07:41,410 --> 01:07:43,970
. . .my nose has been working that great.

1025
01:07:44,570 --> 01:07:46,242
So l've got to ask you. . .

1026
01:07:46,850 --> 01:07:48,647
. . .did you kill that woman or not?

1027
01:07:49,690 --> 01:07:50,600
What?

1028
01:07:53,700 --> 01:07:57,136
What happened at that store that day
Amy Wilson was shot?

1029
01:08:01,820 --> 01:08:04,459
l went into the store to buy
a bottle of A-1 Sauce.

1030
01:08:04,700 --> 01:08:06,292
You paid at the counter--

1031
01:08:06,540 --> 01:08:08,053
No, l never got it.

1032
01:08:08,660 --> 01:08:11,811
l told everybody this.
Why are you asking me this?

1033
01:08:13,380 --> 01:08:15,416
Tell it again. To me.

1034
01:08:20,500 --> 01:08:22,218
l went into the store. . .

1035
01:08:22,780 --> 01:08:25,089
. . .to buy a bottle of A-1 Sauce.

1036
01:08:25,780 --> 01:08:28,692
l didn't know where it was.
Amy was behind the counter.

1037
01:08:28,940 --> 01:08:31,329
Hey, Amy.
Where you keep the steak sauce?

1038
01:08:31,580 --> 01:08:34,697
lt's in the back. See where the
ketchup and relish is?

1039
01:08:35,620 --> 01:08:37,372
l've been meaning to talk to you.

1040
01:08:38,220 --> 01:08:39,733
l don't have it.

1041
01:08:39,980 --> 01:08:43,256
l mean l could give you 30 now,
but l don't have it all.

1042
01:08:44,020 --> 01:08:45,772
When can you give me the whole 96?

1043
01:08:47,220 --> 01:08:49,131
When l get paid, July 1 5th.

1044
01:08:49,420 --> 01:08:51,695
You're not gonna always do this,
are you?

1045
01:08:51,940 --> 01:08:56,536
No, l swear. lt's just, the end of
school year. We have extra expenses.

1046
01:08:58,780 --> 01:09:00,259
All right, then.

1047
01:09:01,180 --> 01:09:02,135
July 1 5th?

1048
01:09:02,620 --> 01:09:03,973
July 1 5th.

1049
01:09:05,980 --> 01:09:07,254
Mind if l use the bathroom?

1050
01:09:07,580 --> 01:09:09,650
You know where it is, right?

1051
01:09:13,020 --> 01:09:15,170
So you weren't mad about the money?

1052
01:09:16,380 --> 01:09:19,053
l just wanted her to know l didn't
do business that way.

1053
01:09:19,300 --> 01:09:21,097
She was cool. l liked her.

1054
01:09:21,580 --> 01:09:23,013
Were you carrying a gun?

1055
01:09:25,940 --> 01:09:26,975
So then what?

1056
01:09:31,060 --> 01:09:33,938
l asked her, could l use her restroom.

1057
01:09:34,180 --> 01:09:37,809
l went in to use the restroom,
and the next thing l know. . .

1058
01:09:38,300 --> 01:09:39,779
. . .there was a gunshot.

1059
01:09:40,900 --> 01:09:41,935
That's all you got?

1060
01:09:42,180 --> 01:09:44,819
lt's the Fourth of July
and we're not that busy.

1061
01:09:45,060 --> 01:09:46,618
-Give me the chain!
-Not that!

1062
01:09:46,860 --> 01:09:48,498
Give me the fucking chain!

1063
01:10:02,620 --> 01:10:04,053
Oh, God. Amy!

1064
01:10:08,580 --> 01:10:09,774
Oh, Jesus!

1065
01:10:13,380 --> 01:10:14,449
Oh, God!

1066
01:10:16,900 --> 01:10:18,015
Sweet Jesus!

1067
01:10:21,060 --> 01:10:22,209
Can you breathe, Amy?

1068
01:10:29,980 --> 01:10:31,891
Somebody help us!

1069
01:10:46,380 --> 01:10:47,449
Anybody here?

1070
01:11:11,420 --> 01:11:12,455
Help!

1071
01:11:13,020 --> 01:11:15,488
-''Please, not that. ''
-That's what l heard.

1072
01:11:15,740 --> 01:11:17,093
Why'd you run?

1073
01:11:17,540 --> 01:11:21,089
lt was stupid. But l've been
running from something most of my life.

1074
01:11:21,540 --> 01:11:24,338
There l was, covered in blood
next to a dead girl. . .

1075
01:11:24,580 --> 01:11:27,811
. . .a white man staring at me
like l was-- l just panicked.

1076
01:11:28,220 --> 01:11:29,733
-Who shot her?
-l don't know.

1077
01:11:30,500 --> 01:11:32,138
Did Porterhouse see the gun?

1078
01:11:32,380 --> 01:11:34,336
-You got five minutes.
-Wasn't no gun!

1079
01:11:34,580 --> 01:11:35,729
Did he see the shooter?

1080
01:11:35,980 --> 01:11:37,015
How would l know?

1081
01:11:37,260 --> 01:11:38,409
Of course he didn't.

1082
01:11:38,660 --> 01:11:41,379
By the time he pulled in the lot,
the shooter had left.

1083
01:11:41,620 --> 01:11:43,497
That's why he didn't hear the shots.

1084
01:11:44,700 --> 01:11:46,338
l don't know when anything happened.

1085
01:11:46,580 --> 01:11:50,289
That's because you were on the floor
trying to save Amy's life.

1086
01:11:50,620 --> 01:11:53,771
What was this, a random shooting?
Or was someone else there?

1087
01:11:54,020 --> 01:11:56,136
l don't know.
l didn't see anything.

1088
01:11:56,380 --> 01:11:57,369
Give me something!

1089
01:11:57,620 --> 01:12:00,339
What do you want?
What do you people want?

1090
01:12:00,580 --> 01:12:01,899
That's it.

1091
01:12:02,820 --> 01:12:06,256
You believe us, don't you?
Do you believe us?

1092
01:12:06,940 --> 01:12:08,931
-Bonnie, don't.
-Do you believe us?

1093
01:12:09,580 --> 01:12:11,730
Yes! l believe you.

1094
01:12:11,980 --> 01:12:12,890
For chrissake!

1095
01:12:13,140 --> 01:12:15,700
Where's your heart?
Don't these people have enough?

1096
01:12:15,940 --> 01:12:17,453
Then where were you?

1097
01:12:19,020 --> 01:12:22,410
Dear God! Where were you
all this time?

1098
01:12:22,940 --> 01:12:25,659
lt wasn't my story.
There was an accident--

1099
01:12:29,180 --> 01:12:31,011
Where were you?

1100
01:12:37,100 --> 01:12:38,579
Everett?

1101
01:12:40,300 --> 01:12:41,733
Warden.

1102
01:12:42,700 --> 01:12:45,339
You know, people come
in here, the press.

1103
01:12:45,580 --> 01:12:49,698
Prisoners tell them things.
All kind of heart-wrenching things.

1104
01:12:50,220 --> 01:12:54,452
And the next day in the paper,
we come off sounding like hard guys.

1105
01:12:55,020 --> 01:12:57,011
lt can get pretty frustrating, is all.

1106
01:12:57,260 --> 01:12:58,818
Yeah, of course.

1107
01:12:59,100 --> 01:13:01,694
We have to do what
the state tells us to do.

1108
01:13:02,780 --> 01:13:04,008
Makes it tough on us. . .

1109
01:13:04,260 --> 01:13:07,730
. . .if we show up in the paper
as bloody murderers.

1110
01:13:09,300 --> 01:13:12,212
Yeah, l understand. Completely.

1111
01:13:12,660 --> 01:13:14,013
Knew you would.

1112
01:13:16,180 --> 01:13:19,411
These things go through all kind
of trials and appeals. . .

1113
01:13:19,660 --> 01:13:21,571
. . .before they get to us.

1114
01:13:22,780 --> 01:13:25,419
No use trying to figure out
who's naughty or nice. . .

1115
01:13:25,660 --> 01:13:28,857
. . .and then come sliding down the
chimney like a hero.

1116
01:13:29,500 --> 01:13:31,252
Not on execution day.

1117
01:13:33,140 --> 01:13:34,858
You're not Santa Claus.

1118
01:13:37,420 --> 01:13:39,729
No such thing as Santa Claus.

1119
01:13:48,260 --> 01:13:49,215
Warden?

1120
01:13:51,940 --> 01:13:53,771
You're not really sure, are you?

1121
01:14:00,740 --> 01:14:02,617
You drive safe now.

1122
01:14:15,100 --> 01:14:17,170
-Cecilia, l want to talk.
-Not a good time.

1123
01:14:17,420 --> 01:14:18,648
Not now. Call my office.

1124
01:14:18,900 --> 01:14:21,050
-This is important.
-Please, just back up.

1125
01:14:21,700 --> 01:14:22,735
Back off, will you?

1126
01:14:22,980 --> 01:14:24,698
What are you, a court attorney?

1127
01:14:24,940 --> 01:14:27,374
Hit a reporter.
See how long you keep your job.

1128
01:14:27,620 --> 01:14:30,134
-Why don't you get in the car?
-Yeah, why don't you?

1129
01:14:31,500 --> 01:14:33,058
New York asshole!

1130
01:14:33,300 --> 01:14:36,178
-What is it?
-Frank Beechum. Who else was there?

1131
01:14:36,420 --> 01:14:37,819
Are you back on the bottle?

1132
01:14:38,060 --> 01:14:41,655
There was Frank Beechum, Nancy
Larson, Porterhouse. . . .

1133
01:14:41,900 --> 01:14:43,618
-Who else?
-What's the difference?

1134
01:14:43,860 --> 01:14:45,657
That's the one who shot Amy.

1135
01:14:46,060 --> 01:14:49,609
l don't know what kind of conspiracy
theory you're working on. . .

1136
01:14:49,860 --> 01:14:53,614
. . .but we've got a solid case.
l don't send innocent men to death.

1137
01:14:53,860 --> 01:14:55,134
l know that. l do.

1138
01:14:55,380 --> 01:14:58,452
But you made a mistake.
He was just using the bathroom.

1139
01:14:58,700 --> 01:15:00,372
He went in for steak sauce.

1140
01:15:01,500 --> 01:15:03,889
You've always been
a gullible son of a bitch.

1141
01:15:04,420 --> 01:15:07,457
Read the transcripts.
A witness saw Beechum with a gun.

1142
01:15:07,700 --> 01:15:10,134
He couldn't have.
Not through the potato chips.

1143
01:15:10,380 --> 01:15:11,699
ls that what he said?

1144
01:15:11,940 --> 01:15:13,692
l saw it in his eyes.
l could tell.

1145
01:15:13,980 --> 01:15:17,052
-You haven't got jack shit.
-How much jack shit do l need?

1146
01:15:17,300 --> 01:15:19,416
There was somebody, wasn't there?

1147
01:15:20,660 --> 01:15:23,891
A kid got a Coke from the machine.
He didn't even look inside.

1148
01:15:24,140 --> 01:15:25,493
He's the one who killed Amy.

1149
01:15:25,740 --> 01:15:28,652
We interviewed him.
We issued a description of his car.

1150
01:15:28,900 --> 01:15:29,776
His story checked out--

1151
01:15:30,020 --> 01:15:32,659
The plain fact is you had
Beechum in custody.

1152
01:15:32,900 --> 01:15:34,731
You didn't have the right person.

1153
01:15:34,980 --> 01:15:36,811
-This was the right guy.
-He was nothing!

1154
01:15:37,060 --> 01:15:41,451
He was in a lineup with Beechum.
Both witnesses still fingered Beechum.

1155
01:15:41,700 --> 01:15:45,659
He was gone before the witnesses
even got there. Just give me his name.

1156
01:15:45,900 --> 01:15:47,811
How can l remember after six years?

1157
01:15:48,060 --> 01:15:50,620
-You've got files!
-He was nothing to the case!

1158
01:15:51,900 --> 01:15:53,891
Call in the morning.
l'll try to help.

1159
01:15:54,140 --> 01:15:57,132
You wait till morning,
you better sleep well tonight.

1160
01:15:57,380 --> 01:16:00,372
Because after today, l'm gonna haunt
the shit out of you.

1161
01:16:00,620 --> 01:16:03,339
l'm gonna haunt your ass all over
this goddamn town.

1162
01:16:04,060 --> 01:16:06,813
l am not Wally.
l'm a lot bigger than Wally.

1163
01:16:07,060 --> 01:16:10,018
Threaten me and l'll have
pieces of you in the gutter. . .

1164
01:16:10,260 --> 01:16:11,773
. . .and l'll blow the rest away.

1165
01:16:16,300 --> 01:16:17,699
One more thing, barfly.

1166
01:16:18,820 --> 01:16:22,256
You ought to know this before your
latest lost cause confesses.

1167
01:16:22,500 --> 01:16:25,697
Did you know Beechum volunteered
for a lie detector test?

1168
01:16:28,900 --> 01:16:32,176
And he flunked it bigtime.
Sure, it's inadmissible.

1169
01:16:32,740 --> 01:16:34,492
lt wasn't
in the transcripts. . .

1170
01:16:34,740 --> 01:16:37,095
. . .but it certainly captured
our attention.

1171
01:16:37,380 --> 01:16:41,168
So why don't you just go pour yourself
a tall one and think about that?

1172
01:17:07,060 --> 01:17:08,175
You want a nip?

1173
01:17:09,180 --> 01:17:10,693
No, thanks. l'd better not.

1174
01:17:10,940 --> 01:17:12,339
Sorry, l forgot.

1175
01:17:15,180 --> 01:17:17,978
What's with Bob? He's been
giving you the evil eye all day.

1176
01:17:18,260 --> 01:17:20,330
Know something?
lt's starting to work.

1177
01:17:20,580 --> 01:17:23,890
Did something happen at the
prison? Some big uproar?

1178
01:17:24,140 --> 01:17:27,689
Why would a guilty man volunteer
for a lie detector test?

1179
01:17:28,060 --> 01:17:31,018
Happens all the time.
Perp thinks he can slide one by.

1180
01:17:31,820 --> 01:17:34,698
Of course, innocent men
flunk them sometimes too.

1181
01:17:35,500 --> 01:17:37,138
Does Bob want you to take one?

1182
01:17:37,420 --> 01:17:39,012
That's a cute idea.

1183
01:17:39,300 --> 01:17:41,575
l don't think
my guilt's in any doubt.

1184
01:17:41,820 --> 01:17:44,493
Where's Bridget?
l want her to do some scutwork.

1185
01:17:44,740 --> 01:17:47,334
Women feel much more secure
in the workplace now.

1186
01:17:47,580 --> 01:17:50,174
She left. But l'll get
your coffee if you give me head.

1187
01:17:54,020 --> 01:17:57,695
Better yet, track down an
investigator in the Beechum case.

1188
01:17:57,940 --> 01:17:59,339
See if there was another. . .

1189
01:17:59,780 --> 01:18:00,974
. . .witness on the scene.

1190
01:18:01,220 --> 01:18:03,529
A kid. Just an address
and a name will do.

1191
01:18:03,780 --> 01:18:04,849
You got it.

1192
01:18:05,300 --> 01:18:06,892
After that, get me some coffee.

1193
01:18:14,740 --> 01:18:16,458
Oakland Police.
Sgt. Bartlett.

1194
01:18:16,700 --> 01:18:19,897
Donaldson at the Tribune.
Who headed the Beechum case?

1195
01:18:20,140 --> 01:18:22,256
Anyone there know the Beechum case?

1196
01:18:22,540 --> 01:18:24,132
All of us. Anyone here.

1197
01:18:24,380 --> 01:18:26,132
Before Beechum comes to the store. . .

1198
01:18:26,380 --> 01:18:29,417
. . .there's another witness
in the parking lot, right?

1199
01:18:29,660 --> 01:18:32,493
Wrong. There's nothing
like that in the files.

1200
01:18:32,740 --> 01:18:35,857
-How do you know? Have you looked?
-Believe me, we know.

1201
01:18:36,100 --> 01:18:38,295
Everybody here has
memorized these files.

1202
01:18:38,540 --> 01:18:41,612
No other witnesses.
Porterhouse and Larson, that's it.

1203
01:18:41,860 --> 01:18:43,657
But a lot of circumstantial.

1204
01:18:43,900 --> 01:18:45,811
This is Donaldson at the Tribune.

1205
01:18:46,060 --> 01:18:49,336
On the Beechum case, was there
a record of a kid who was a witness?

1206
01:18:49,580 --> 01:18:50,569
A kid?

1207
01:18:51,420 --> 01:18:52,819
l don 't think so.

1208
01:18:53,260 --> 01:18:55,774
-You're sure?
-Thanks anyway.

1209
01:18:56,140 --> 01:18:57,175
All right, thanks.

1210
01:19:02,180 --> 01:19:04,250
That was the whip in the investigation.

1211
01:19:04,580 --> 01:19:07,731
Says it rings a bell.
But he doesn't remember any names.

1212
01:19:08,020 --> 01:19:12,093
Ardsley, who headed the investigation,
retired. Florida somewhere.

1213
01:19:12,500 --> 01:19:13,694
Shit!

1214
01:19:15,460 --> 01:19:17,212
Everett! Come here.

1215
01:19:18,100 --> 01:19:19,499
Shit!

1216
01:19:24,820 --> 01:19:28,017
-Don't look so happy about it.
-Who said anything about being happy?

1217
01:19:28,260 --> 01:19:32,458
l understand your prison interview went
beyond just a human-interest sidebar.

1218
01:19:32,700 --> 01:19:36,215
l colored outside the lines a bit,
but the warden wasn't sore about it.

1219
01:19:36,460 --> 01:19:39,179
He just probably thought
you were back on the booze.

1220
01:19:39,420 --> 01:19:42,014
-There's no smoking in the building.
-You got a minute?!

1221
01:19:42,260 --> 01:19:43,375
l can't tolerate this.

1222
01:19:43,620 --> 01:19:46,214
Steve, say you're sorry.
Bob, punch his lights out.

1223
01:19:46,460 --> 01:19:47,654
This isn't personal.

1224
01:19:47,900 --> 01:19:50,619
l gave him an important story
with specific instructions.

1225
01:19:50,860 --> 01:19:52,054
The newspaper promised--

1226
01:19:52,300 --> 01:19:54,336
-The guy is not guilty.
-Come on!

1227
01:19:54,580 --> 01:19:57,811
This isn't a human-interest sidebar.
lt's a crucifixion.

1228
01:19:58,060 --> 01:20:01,450
Want me to look at the cross and say
''How's the weather up there?''

1229
01:20:01,700 --> 01:20:04,658
l've got all the personal crap
here in this book.

1230
01:20:05,260 --> 01:20:07,933
He believes in God.
Thinks he's going to heaven.

1231
01:20:08,180 --> 01:20:10,853
He's happy as shit.
He's glad they're juicing him.

1232
01:20:11,100 --> 01:20:13,170
-Go write your sidebar!
-That's not the point.

1233
01:20:13,420 --> 01:20:14,819
Of course it's not the point.

1234
01:20:15,060 --> 01:20:18,370
Fine. Take Steve off the
execution and put Harvey on it.

1235
01:20:18,620 --> 01:20:21,657
-That's still not the point.
-We know what the point is.

1236
01:20:21,980 --> 01:20:23,459
l can't work with you, Steve.

1237
01:20:23,780 --> 01:20:24,929
You're a good reporter. . .

1238
01:20:25,180 --> 01:20:28,855
. . .but there's plenty of good
reporters here who follow instructions.

1239
01:20:29,100 --> 01:20:30,089
l can't work with him.

1240
01:20:30,340 --> 01:20:32,058
Why don't you hit me in the face?

1241
01:20:32,300 --> 01:20:33,733
l'll fall down. l'll bleed.

1242
01:20:33,980 --> 01:20:35,857
l'll do all that. l deserve it.

1243
01:20:36,100 --> 01:20:38,739
Then go home and hit your wife.
She likes it.

1244
01:20:43,500 --> 01:20:44,774
Nice one, babe.

1245
01:20:46,540 --> 01:20:49,691
We can't all live in the world
of your imagination.

1246
01:20:49,940 --> 01:20:53,489
l won't hit anybody, because that's
exactly what you'd want.

1247
01:20:53,740 --> 01:20:57,779
lf Patricia needs to find something
outside our marriage, she can find it.

1248
01:20:58,020 --> 01:21:00,170
My marriage isn't your business,
number one.

1249
01:21:00,420 --> 01:21:02,729
Number two, you're a thoughtless. . .

1250
01:21:02,980 --> 01:21:05,574
. . .unbalanced man.
l can't work with him!

1251
01:21:05,820 --> 01:21:07,731
l've enjoyed this episode of Oprah--

1252
01:21:07,980 --> 01:21:09,254
l got the shooter.

1253
01:21:11,500 --> 01:21:15,493
-We shouldn't confuse the issues.
-l got the guy who killed Amy Wilson.

1254
01:21:15,740 --> 01:21:18,732
-Even if it's the guy who shot JFK--
-Bob, shut up!

1255
01:21:18,980 --> 01:21:20,174
How have you got him?

1256
01:21:20,500 --> 01:21:22,297
l've got him. l know who he is.

1257
01:21:23,180 --> 01:21:24,374
All right, who is he?

1258
01:21:24,620 --> 01:21:27,453
He's a guy.
He's a guy who was there.

1259
01:21:30,380 --> 01:21:34,009
You're telling me that the shooter
is a guy who was there?

1260
01:21:34,700 --> 01:21:38,056
Great! Should l hold the front
page or wait for two sources?

1261
01:21:38,300 --> 01:21:39,938
The D.A. won't give me the name.

1262
01:21:40,180 --> 01:21:43,138
-What about the defense?
-The defense doesn't have it.

1263
01:21:43,500 --> 01:21:44,615
This is ridiculous.

1264
01:21:46,420 --> 01:21:47,614
Shut. . .

1265
01:21:47,820 --> 01:21:48,616
. . .up.

1266
01:21:50,580 --> 01:21:52,013
What about the cops?

1267
01:21:52,940 --> 01:21:54,453
They're sitting on it.

1268
01:21:54,700 --> 01:21:55,610
Jesus!

1269
01:21:55,860 --> 01:21:58,010
Sorry, Alan. This is just too much.

1270
01:21:58,620 --> 01:22:01,054
Alan, l gotta be clear
on this, okay?

1271
01:22:01,300 --> 01:22:03,416
This is causing problems for everybody.

1272
01:22:03,660 --> 01:22:05,571
l love the paper
but l'm ready to go.

1273
01:22:05,820 --> 01:22:09,574
l can't work like this.
This environment's become intolerable.

1274
01:22:09,820 --> 01:22:12,175
''lntolerable environment''?
Are you a feminist?

1275
01:22:12,420 --> 01:22:14,536
Are you a cooze?
What's wrong with you?

1276
01:22:14,780 --> 01:22:16,418
You gotta give me notice.

1277
01:22:19,580 --> 01:22:22,652
My contract says if you dump me,
you gotta give me notice.

1278
01:22:23,380 --> 01:22:25,052
How much notice do you want?

1279
01:22:27,900 --> 01:22:30,175
Six hours and seven minutes.

1280
01:22:39,580 --> 01:22:41,650
Testing red. Testing red.

1281
01:22:44,260 --> 01:22:46,728
Testing tan. Testing tan.

1282
01:22:49,420 --> 01:22:51,297
Testing white. Testing white.

1283
01:22:52,940 --> 01:22:55,295
Testing black.

1284
01:22:59,620 --> 01:23:01,736
We're in San Quentin 's
gas chamber...

1285
01:23:01,980 --> 01:23:04,050
...now converted
for lethal injection.

1286
01:23:04,300 --> 01:23:07,497
The first syringe delivers five grams
of sodium Pentothal...

1287
01:23:07,740 --> 01:23:11,255
...and that will put him to sleep
within a few seconds.

1288
01:23:11,500 --> 01:23:15,573
Then the injection line is flushed
with 20 cc's of saline solution...

1289
01:23:15,820 --> 01:23:19,290
...and then he'll be given 50 cc's
of pancuronium bromide.

1290
01:23:19,580 --> 01:23:22,777
Now that is a muscle paralyzer,
and at that point...

1291
01:23:23,020 --> 01:23:24,692
...he won 't be able to breathe.

1292
01:23:24,940 --> 01:23:28,057
And finally, 50 cc's
of potassium chloride.

1293
01:23:28,300 --> 01:23:30,256
And that'll stop his heart.

1294
01:24:02,300 --> 01:24:03,938
Yes, this is--

1295
01:24:04,700 --> 01:24:07,294
This is Steve's wife. Why?

1296
01:24:08,980 --> 01:24:11,414
What's the matter?
Something happen to him?

1297
01:24:36,260 --> 01:24:37,773
Already, the vultures come--

1298
01:24:39,460 --> 01:24:41,018
So steal. Go ahead.

1299
01:24:41,260 --> 01:24:42,659
Mr. Ziegler?

1300
01:24:45,180 --> 01:24:46,499
l'm not a thief.

1301
01:24:46,740 --> 01:24:49,652
l'm a friend of Michelle's,
a colleague at the paper.

1302
01:24:50,300 --> 01:24:52,370
My friends, most of them knock.

1303
01:24:53,780 --> 01:24:55,133
l'm sorry.

1304
01:24:56,100 --> 01:24:59,172
l'm sorry about Michelle.
She was really topnotch.

1305
01:24:59,420 --> 01:25:01,490
A really fine reporter.

1306
01:25:02,660 --> 01:25:04,571
So you came to give the eulogy?

1307
01:25:04,820 --> 01:25:06,253
Michelle was on a story.

1308
01:25:06,700 --> 01:25:10,295
A man will be executed tonight.
l think he's innocent.

1309
01:25:10,540 --> 01:25:13,338
l think the answer may be in
Michelle's papers.

1310
01:25:14,860 --> 01:25:15,929
Something Michelle did?

1311
01:25:16,180 --> 01:25:17,772
Something she was onto, yeah.

1312
01:25:18,860 --> 01:25:19,849
So look!

1313
01:25:20,100 --> 01:25:21,215
Great.

1314
01:25:23,020 --> 01:25:25,215
l've been going through her things too.

1315
01:25:26,060 --> 01:25:27,539
See this?

1316
01:25:28,220 --> 01:25:30,780
Gave her this when she was 9.
She loved it.

1317
01:25:33,820 --> 01:25:35,014
She saved everything.

1318
01:25:36,780 --> 01:25:38,008
Look at this.

1319
01:25:38,260 --> 01:25:41,696
l don't know when she did it.
Must have been 4 or 5.

1320
01:25:45,460 --> 01:25:47,416
Where'd this come from? Over here?

1321
01:25:55,540 --> 01:25:56,973
This anything?

1322
01:25:57,220 --> 01:25:59,859
''Warren Russel, 1 7 years old.

1323
01:26:00,100 --> 01:26:03,888
4331 Knight Street. lnterviewed
July 7th at own request. ''

1324
01:26:05,020 --> 01:26:08,410
''Says he bought a soda and left.
Saw nothing.

1325
01:26:08,900 --> 01:26:10,891
Something fishy here. ''

1326
01:26:12,620 --> 01:26:16,579
Mr. Ziegler, that Michelle, she was
really on top of things.

1327
01:26:16,820 --> 01:26:18,094
Great!

1328
01:26:31,540 --> 01:26:32,893
Sorry, Frank.

1329
01:26:33,260 --> 01:26:35,728
We'll have to ask Mrs. Beechum
to leave now.

1330
01:26:36,580 --> 01:26:37,979
Give us a minute, okay?

1331
01:26:39,900 --> 01:26:40,935
Sure.

1332
01:26:44,380 --> 01:26:46,371
l don't think l can do this.

1333
01:26:50,940 --> 01:26:53,693
l won't get a chance
to say goodbye later on.

1334
01:26:58,220 --> 01:27:01,974
So l need you to take care
of yourself and our little girl.

1335
01:27:02,940 --> 01:27:04,737
You know l will, baby.

1336
01:27:05,300 --> 01:27:06,892
-l will.
-And give her this.

1337
01:27:07,500 --> 01:27:08,979
And don't forget.

1338
01:27:10,860 --> 01:27:12,373
lt ain't much, but it's--

1339
01:27:12,620 --> 01:27:14,736
lt'll be precious to her.

1340
01:27:15,620 --> 01:27:17,770
lt will be her most precious thing.

1341
01:27:19,860 --> 01:27:22,579
l really hate that
you have to go through this.

1342
01:27:23,460 --> 01:27:24,779
l know.

1343
01:27:25,860 --> 01:27:26,770
Okay, l love you.

1344
01:27:27,020 --> 01:27:28,772
l love you.

1345
01:27:30,260 --> 01:27:32,251
l wanted to be there for you.

1346
01:27:32,500 --> 01:27:35,139
God knows l wanted to see
my little girl grow up.

1347
01:27:37,260 --> 01:27:38,978
lf we just had more time--

1348
01:27:39,500 --> 01:27:42,333
We have to be thankful
for the time we had.

1349
01:27:42,580 --> 01:27:43,933
lt's that it was short.

1350
01:27:44,420 --> 01:27:45,614
At least we made Gail.

1351
01:27:45,860 --> 01:27:47,498
We made Gail together.

1352
01:27:47,740 --> 01:27:50,095
We made something beautiful
in this world.

1353
01:27:50,900 --> 01:27:53,937
You look at her and remember
how much l love you.

1354
01:27:54,660 --> 01:27:55,775
Can you do that?

1355
01:27:56,660 --> 01:27:58,173
God, Frank, l'm so scared.

1356
01:27:59,500 --> 01:28:00,728
lf l can see your face--

1357
01:28:00,980 --> 01:28:02,652
l'll talk to you every day.

1358
01:28:03,620 --> 01:28:05,850
-lf l can see you at the end.
-Come with me!

1359
01:28:06,100 --> 01:28:08,091
You going to be talking to me?

1360
01:28:08,940 --> 01:28:10,168
lf l could see your face!

1361
01:28:10,420 --> 01:28:12,809
How did this ever happen to us?

1362
01:28:18,900 --> 01:28:21,460
The only thing in my life. . .

1363
01:28:21,740 --> 01:28:23,776
. . .that made it worth anything.

1364
01:28:24,860 --> 01:28:27,135
God bless you for that.

1365
01:28:30,020 --> 01:28:32,693
God bless you for that.

1366
01:28:37,540 --> 01:28:38,689
Who's there?

1367
01:28:40,460 --> 01:28:43,577
l'm Steve Everett. l'm a reporter
for the Tribune.

1368
01:28:55,100 --> 01:28:56,453
Go home!

1369
01:28:58,020 --> 01:29:00,250
And quit casing that man's car.

1370
01:29:01,180 --> 01:29:02,818
lt's almost your dinnertime.

1371
01:29:03,060 --> 01:29:04,288
Go home!

1372
01:29:08,860 --> 01:29:11,249
-Sorry about them kids.
-That's all right.

1373
01:29:11,500 --> 01:29:13,297
l'm just glad to find you here.

1374
01:29:14,220 --> 01:29:16,609
What, you thought l moved
to the suburbs?

1375
01:29:19,300 --> 01:29:20,528
Come on in.

1376
01:29:26,580 --> 01:29:27,808
And you are. . .?

1377
01:29:28,060 --> 01:29:29,015
Angela Russel.

1378
01:29:29,260 --> 01:29:30,295
And Warren?

1379
01:29:30,980 --> 01:29:32,129
My grandson.

1380
01:29:35,140 --> 01:29:36,334
ls this Warren here?

1381
01:29:36,780 --> 01:29:38,008
lt is.

1382
01:29:38,260 --> 01:29:40,012
Want to tell me why you're here?

1383
01:29:41,540 --> 01:29:44,532
Mrs. Russel, it's important
that l talk to Warren.

1384
01:29:44,780 --> 01:29:46,975
lt's important l talk to him tonight.

1385
01:29:47,220 --> 01:29:51,259
lt is? And what could be so important,
if you don't mind my asking?

1386
01:29:51,780 --> 01:29:55,659
There's a man on death row, and
they're gonna execute him tonight.

1387
01:29:56,260 --> 01:29:58,410
They say he killed
a store clerk. . .

1388
01:29:58,660 --> 01:30:00,571
. . .six years ago. An Amy Wilson.

1389
01:30:00,860 --> 01:30:02,134
l think he's innocent.

1390
01:30:02,380 --> 01:30:04,689
l think Warren knows
something about it.

1391
01:30:04,940 --> 01:30:06,976
Why would you
think a thing like that?

1392
01:30:07,700 --> 01:30:09,975
He's the only other person
that was there.

1393
01:30:11,420 --> 01:30:12,739
And how do we know that?

1394
01:30:13,540 --> 01:30:15,770
The witnesses didn't see anyone else.

1395
01:30:16,740 --> 01:30:21,052
Wait a minute. There were witnesses,
even though nobody else was there?

1396
01:30:21,300 --> 01:30:24,133
-Yes, that's right--
-No, wait. Help me out here.

1397
01:30:24,460 --> 01:30:26,212
l am getting confused.

1398
01:30:26,500 --> 01:30:28,934
There was an accountant
and a housewife.

1399
01:30:30,660 --> 01:30:31,854
White people?

1400
01:30:36,260 --> 01:30:37,534
And l bet. . .

1401
01:30:37,780 --> 01:30:40,533
. . .that girl that got killed,
that Amy Wilson. . .

1402
01:30:40,780 --> 01:30:42,577
. . .she was white too, wasn't she?

1403
01:30:43,220 --> 01:30:45,290
That's right. But l don't think--

1404
01:30:45,540 --> 01:30:48,008
You don't think those nice
white people. . .

1405
01:30:48,260 --> 01:30:50,216
. . .would kill that nice white girl.

1406
01:30:50,580 --> 01:30:52,298
But they all looked around. . .

1407
01:30:52,620 --> 01:30:55,498
. . .and what do you know?
There was a black boy.

1408
01:30:56,780 --> 01:30:57,974
Look, it isn't like that.

1409
01:30:58,220 --> 01:31:01,690
Will you just think back
in your mind? Six years ago.

1410
01:31:01,940 --> 01:31:04,659
Was Warren using drugs
or anything like that?

1411
01:31:04,900 --> 01:31:06,049
He was into drugs.

1412
01:31:06,300 --> 01:31:07,415
Did he own a gun?

1413
01:31:07,660 --> 01:31:10,970
They all own guns, Mr. Everett.
Don't you know that?

1414
01:31:11,220 --> 01:31:15,133
All those black dope-fiend boys,
they all own guns.

1415
01:31:16,380 --> 01:31:17,574
Can l just talk to him?

1416
01:31:17,820 --> 01:31:19,458
Do you know where he is?

1417
01:31:21,580 --> 01:31:22,979
Yes, l do.

1418
01:31:23,900 --> 01:31:25,572
And no, you can't.

1419
01:31:25,900 --> 01:31:29,529
Look, an innocent man
is gonna die tonight.

1420
01:31:30,500 --> 01:31:32,695
l have seen a lot of innocent folk. . .

1421
01:31:32,940 --> 01:31:36,012
. . .die in this part of town,
Mr. Everett.

1422
01:31:36,540 --> 01:31:37,734
But it's funny.

1423
01:31:38,260 --> 01:31:41,252
l ain't never seen you
around here before.

1424
01:31:41,580 --> 01:31:45,619
Mrs. Russel, you're making this into
a racial thing, and it isn't.

1425
01:31:45,860 --> 01:31:48,249
The man on death row,
he's a black man too.

1426
01:31:48,500 --> 01:31:49,899
Did you know that?

1427
01:31:50,140 --> 01:31:54,258
They'll kill him at midnight.
l can't help unless l have the facts.

1428
01:31:54,820 --> 01:31:57,857
The only fact l know, Mr. Everett. . .

1429
01:31:58,660 --> 01:32:00,571
. . .is that my grandson, Warren. . .

1430
01:32:01,060 --> 01:32:04,530
. . .he's been in his grave now
going on three years.

1431
01:32:04,900 --> 01:32:08,210
Stabbed out there in the park.

1432
01:32:14,580 --> 01:32:16,218
My Warren. . .

1433
01:32:16,460 --> 01:32:18,530
. . .was a loving child.

1434
01:32:19,260 --> 01:32:21,649
But l don't remember you
coming around. . .

1435
01:32:21,900 --> 01:32:25,131
. . .looking for the facts
when he was killed.

1436
01:32:25,900 --> 01:32:29,734
Nobody came around here
looking for the facts then.

1437
01:32:36,060 --> 01:32:37,334
Fucking loser!

1438
01:32:37,580 --> 01:32:39,411
Goddamn it!

1439
01:32:44,980 --> 01:32:47,813
We're told he's having
the last meal he requested...

1440
01:32:48,060 --> 01:32:50,016
...steak and french fries.
Oddly enough...

1441
01:32:50,260 --> 01:32:52,820
...he also requested two
six-packs of Coke.

1442
01:32:53,060 --> 01:32:56,336
lf you're just tuning in,
we'll repeat our top story.

1443
01:32:56,580 --> 01:33:01,290
Convicted killer Frank Beechum has,
for the first time, confessed his crime.

1444
01:33:01,780 --> 01:33:03,771
The confession was made
to the chaplain...

1445
01:33:04,020 --> 01:33:05,419
...as an expression of remorse...

1446
01:33:05,660 --> 01:33:09,653
...for the murder of Amy Wilson
and her unborn child six years ago.

1447
01:33:09,900 --> 01:33:13,256
A source in the governor's office
says despite this...

1448
01:33:13,500 --> 01:33:17,857
... the execution will proceed
at one minute after midnight tonight.

1449
01:33:18,100 --> 01:33:20,898
And in other news, the market
slumped badly....

1450
01:33:59,020 --> 01:34:00,976
l am tired.

1451
01:34:01,220 --> 01:34:03,051
Aren't you supposed to be sleeping?

1452
01:34:03,300 --> 01:34:05,609
Why are you here, Daddy?

1453
01:34:08,500 --> 01:34:11,060
l'm here to see you, you little goon.

1454
01:34:12,660 --> 01:34:14,252
Where did you go?

1455
01:34:16,020 --> 01:34:17,692
A wild-goose chase.

1456
01:34:17,940 --> 01:34:19,692
You went chasing?

1457
01:34:22,540 --> 01:34:25,418
Chasing salvation.
Never did find it.

1458
01:34:25,940 --> 01:34:27,214
Just disappeared.

1459
01:34:34,940 --> 01:34:35,816
Let me tell you. . . .

1460
01:34:36,060 --> 01:34:37,937
About today, l'm sorry.

1461
01:34:39,300 --> 01:34:40,619
Maybe this weekend we'll. . .

1462
01:34:40,860 --> 01:34:43,818
. . .go and spend the whole day?
Play Slow Zoo.

1463
01:34:46,540 --> 01:34:48,212
And this time, could we see. . .

1464
01:34:48,460 --> 01:34:50,257
. . .the hippopotamus?

1465
01:34:50,500 --> 01:34:53,298
l've already talked to him.
We have an appointment.

1466
01:34:55,940 --> 01:34:57,532
My little Daddy.

1467
01:34:57,780 --> 01:35:00,010
l'll go to sleep now.

1468
01:35:00,260 --> 01:35:03,411
Okay, l think that's a good idea.

1469
01:35:08,860 --> 01:35:10,293
Close them, now.

1470
01:35:47,820 --> 01:35:49,139
lf this were a bullet. . .

1471
01:35:55,020 --> 01:35:56,578
